The person exists or has existed, thus the resource can be represented by an IRI for *a* person (not necessarily a blank node (anonymous resource)), but the information to identify the person is missing. This knowledge of absence of certain information is made explicit. In other words, there is a distinction between the IRI identifying *a* person, and the information, provided by properties, e.g. birth date, family name, christian name, permitting to sufficiently describe thé person to be identified.
